Name: cervical mucinous adenocarcinoma
Definition: A cervical adenocarcinoma that derives_from mucin producing epithelial cells.
Synonym: primary malignant neoplasm of olfactory nerve

Name: cervical clear cell adenocarcinoma
Definition: A cervical adenocarcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells which have clear cytoplasm.
Synonym: Clear cell carcinoma of the Cervix Uteri

Name: Wolffian duct adenocarcinoma
Definition: A cervical adenocarcinoma that has_material_basis_in remnants of mesonephric ducts and is located anywhere along the length between the ovary and vagina in sites of remnant wolffian ducts.

Name: obsolete ovine progressive interstitial pneumonia
Definition: A viral infectious disease that results_in inflammation located_in lungs

Name: cervical serous adenocarcinoma
Definition: A cervical adenocarcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells originating in glandular tissue forming serous lesions.

Name: cervical endometrioid adenocarcinoma
Definition: A cervical adenocarcinoma that derives_from endometrial epithelial cells of glandular origin.
Synonym: endometrioid carcinoma of the Cervix Uteri

Name: early invasive cervical adenocarcinoma
Definition: A cervical adenocarcinoma that is characterized by tumor cells that are identical to those in adenocarcinoma in situ (ACIS) and mcroscopic findings that suggest invasion.

Name: obsolete metastatic carcinoma from the small bowel
Definition: A cervical adenocarcinoma that is characterized by tumor cells that are identical to those in adenocarcinoma in situ (ACIS) and mcroscopic findings that suggest invasion.
Synonym: metastatic carcinoma from the small Intestine
